{
  "doc_id": "14958",
  "text": "The steepness of the Mg 2+ -dependent folding transition, n, is directly proportional to the change in folding free energy with lnC. Fractional populations of I C and N were calculated from fits to experimental folding transitions [CITATION_1] ; the average parameters and two-state approximation were used to determine the free energy changes associated with the U to I C and I C to N folding steps at a common [Mg 2+ ], C ref , using ΔG(C) = ÀnRT ln(C ref /C m ) [CITATION_2] . Values of C ref were 0.8 mM for U to I C (SAXS) and 5 mM for I C to N (activity), and were chosen to represent the same point (90% saturation) along U to I and I to N equilibria for the WT ribozyme. In both cases, C ref is close to the transition midpoint, where the assumption of constant n is likely valid [CITATION_3] .",
